# OpenBrain MCP credentials — copy to ~/.config/openbrain/.env and fill in.
#
#   cp .openbrain/env.example ~/.config/openbrain/.env
#   chmod 600 ~/.config/openbrain/.env
#
# This file (env.example) is tracked in git; the real .env is NOT.
# Never put real secrets in this file.
#
# The bootstrap/setup.sh wizard generates this file for you on first run.
# After that, add/remove accounts by re-running:
#   ./bootstrap/lib/add-google-account.sh <email>
#   ./bootstrap/lib/add-slack-workspace.sh <subdomain>
#   ./bootstrap/lib/add-asana.sh personal|work
#   ./bootstrap/lib/add-fathom.sh

# =============================================================================
# Asana — one personal account, one work account, both optional
# Generate PATs at: https://app.asana.com/0/my-apps
# =============================================================================
ASANA_PAT_PERSONAL=
ASANA_PAT_WORK=

# =============================================================================
# Google — one shared OAuth client, per-account refresh tokens
#
# One-time setup (per machine):
#   1. https://console.cloud.google.com → create project "openbrain-mcp"
#   2. APIs & Services → Library → enable:
#        Gmail API, Google Calendar API, Google Meet REST API,
#        Google Drive API, Google Docs API, Google Sheets API,
#        Google Slides API
#   3. OAuth consent screen → External
#      - app name: OpenBrain MCP
#      - scopes: .../auth/gmail.modify, .../auth/calendar,
#                .../auth/meetings.space.readonly, .../auth/drive.readonly,
#                .../auth/drive, .../auth/documents,
#                .../auth/spreadsheets, .../auth/presentations
#      - test users: add EVERY Google account you want to wire up
#   4. Credentials → Create OAuth client ID → Desktop app → "openbrain-mcp-desktop"
#   5. Copy client id + secret into the two variables below.
#   6. Run `./bootstrap/lib/add-google-account.sh <email>` per account.
#
# Workspace-admin gotcha: Google Workspace accounts (custom domains)
# may require admin approval of the OAuth client ID in Google Workspace
# admin → Security → API controls → App access control.
# =============================================================================
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Google account slugs are stored below this marker — bootstrap scripts append
# them automatically. No env vars needed for slugs themselves; refresh tokens
# live in ~/.config/openbrain/tokens/ per slug.
# --- GOOGLE_SLUGS (managed by bootstrap) ---
# --- END GOOGLE_SLUGS ---

# =============================================================================
# Slack — one user token (xoxp-*) per workspace
#
# One-time setup (per workspace):
#   1. https://api.slack.com/apps → Create New App → From scratch
#      - name: OpenBrain MCP
#      - workspace: pick the target workspace
#   2. OAuth & Permissions → add User Token Scopes:
#        channels:history, channels:read,
#        groups:history,   groups:read,
#        im:history,       im:read,
#        mpim:history,     mpim:read,
#        users:read, search:read, chat:write
#   3. Install to Workspace → copy the User OAuth Token (xoxp-*)
#   4. Run `./bootstrap/lib/add-slack-workspace.sh <subdomain>` and paste when prompted.
#
# Workspace-admin gotcha: non-admins in managed Slack workspaces may need
# admin approval — Slack will queue the install at
# https://<workspace>.slack.com/apps/manage/requests.
# =============================================================================
# --- SLACK_TOKENS (managed by bootstrap) ---
# --- END SLACK_TOKENS ---

# =============================================================================
# Fathom — AI meeting recorder (optional)
#
# One-time setup:
#   1. Go to https://fathom.video/settings → Integrations → API
#   2. Generate an API key
#   3. Run `./bootstrap/lib/add-fathom.sh` and paste when prompted.
# =============================================================================
FATHOM_API_KEY=
